Textron Posts 6.7% Profit Rise
The commercial products sector, mainly the automotive
divisions, boosted operating profit to $50.7 million from
$32.9 million a year ago, recovering from a
recession-battered first half, Textron said. Revenue rose to
$477.9 million from $439.5 million. Financial services profit
rose to $81.1 million from $75.2 million, as revenue grew to
$677.8 million from $632.7 million.
   But aerospace technology operating profit dropped sharply
to $79.4 million from $100.6 million as revenue declined to
$858 million from $1.07 billion.